%description:
Module test for TI-LFA (RFC 9855) repair-stack COMPUTATION only (Workstream F2, Phase 2) --
no link failure is triggered here (that's a later phase's job, wiring the computed repairs
into LibTable::setBackup()/activateBackup()). This test locks in that ~SegmentRouting, with
`tiLfa=true`, correctly finds a single-segment (PQ node) repair over a real, flooded,
multi-router network -- not just a hand-built unit-test harness.

Topology (a "diamond"): A(1.1.1.1) -- B(2.2.2.2) -- D(4.4.4.4), and also A -- C(3.3.3.3) -- D,
all links metric 1. A's shortest path to D is via B (cost 2); the A-C-D branch (also cost 2)
is a tied-cost alternate. All four nodes share one sidTable (A=1, B=2, C=3, D=4; srgbBase
16000 -> labels A=16001, B=16002, C=16003, D=16004).

With the A-B link (A's own next hop toward D) treated as "protected": excluding it, A can
still reach C (unaffected, direct link) and, via C, D itself -- at the SAME cost as before
(1+1=2), so both C and D remain in A's (distance-preserving) P-space. On the OTHER side,
Q-space of D (nodes whose own path to D doesn't need the A-B link) includes B (direct B-D
link, doesn't touch A-B at all), C, D itself, and -- since A's own alternate via C ties the
original cost -- A too.

P-space = {A, C, D}, Q-space = {A, B, C, D}. Excluding routerId (A) itself from consideration
(pushing "your own" node-SID as a repair is meaningless), the intersection is {C, D}; since
SegmentRouting iterates candidates in ascending IPv4 address order, C (3.3.3.3) is found
BEFORE D (4.4.4.4) -- this deliberately proves the computation finds a genuine INTERMEDIATE
PQ node, not just trivially falling back to the destination itself (which is also technically
a valid, but less interesting, PQ node in this topology).

Expected repair for destination D, protecting the A-B link: a SINGLE node-SID segment, C's
label (16003) -- logged as "TI-LFA repair for 4.4.4.4 via 2.2.2.2: [PUSH 16003 (3.3.3.3)]".

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: test.ned

import inet.node.mpls.SrMplsRouter;
import ned.DatarateChannel;

network TiLfaRepairPqTest
{
    parameters:
        **.ipv4.configurator.networkConfiguratorModule = "";
    types:
        channel Link extends DatarateChannel
        {
            datarate = 1Mbps;
            delay = 10us;
        }
    submodules:
        A: SrMplsRouter {
            parameters:
                routerId = "1.1.1.1";
                peers = "ppp0 ppp1";
                sidTable = xmldoc("sidtable.xml");
                segmentRouting.tiLfa = true;
                @display("p=250,100");
            gates:
                pppg[2];
        }
        B: SrMplsRouter {
            parameters:
                routerId = "2.2.2.2";
                peers = "ppp0 ppp1";
                sidTable = xmldoc("sidtable.xml");
                @display("p=400,50");
            gates:
                pppg[2];
        }
        C: SrMplsRouter {
            parameters:
                routerId = "3.3.3.3";
                peers = "ppp0 ppp1";
                sidTable = xmldoc("sidtable.xml");
                @display("p=400,150");
            gates:
                pppg[2];
        }
        D: SrMplsRouter {
            parameters:
                routerId = "4.4.4.4";
                peers = "ppp0 ppp1";
                sidTable = xmldoc("sidtable.xml");
                @display("p=550,100");
            gates:
                pppg[2];
        }
    connections:
        A.pppg[0] <--> Link <--> B.pppg[0];
        B.pppg[1] <--> Link <--> D.pppg[0];
        A.pppg[1] <--> Link <--> C.pppg[0];
        C.pppg[1] <--> Link <--> D.pppg[1];
}

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: sidtable.xml
<sr>
    <node router="1.1.1.1" sid="1"/>
    <node router="2.2.2.2" sid="2"/>
    <node router="3.3.3.3" sid="3"/>
    <node router="4.4.4.4" sid="4"/>
</sr>

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: A.rt
ifconfig:
name: ppp0	inet_addr: 10.0.1.1	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
name: ppp1	inet_addr: 10.0.1.2	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
ifconfigend.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: B.rt
ifconfig:
name: ppp0	inet_addr: 10.0.1.3	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
name: ppp1	inet_addr: 10.0.1.4	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
ifconfigend.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: C.rt
ifconfig:
name: ppp0	inet_addr: 10.0.1.5	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
name: ppp1	inet_addr: 10.0.1.6	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
ifconfigend.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%file: D.rt
ifconfig:
name: ppp0	inet_addr: 10.0.1.7	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
name: ppp1	inet_addr: 10.0.1.8	MTU: 1500	Metric: 1
ifconfigend.

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
ned-path = .;../../../../src
network = TiLfaRepairPqTest
sim-time-limit = 2s
total-stack = 64MiB
record-vector-results = false
cmdenv-express-mode = false
**.cmdenv-log-level = "detail"
output-scalar-file = "${resultdir}/${configname}-#${runnumber}.sca"

**.A.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "A.rt"
**.B.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "B.rt"
**.C.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "C.rt"
**.D.ipv4.routingTable.routingFile = "D.rt"

**.ppp[*].queue.typename = "DropTailQueue"
**.ppp[*].queue.packetCapacity = 10

%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%# A single node-SID segment (C's label, 16003) repairs destination D against the A-B link.
%contains: stdout
TI-LFA repair for 4.4.4.4 via 2.2.2.2: [PUSH 16003 (3.3.3.3)]
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
%postrun-command: grep "undisposed object:" test.out > test_undisposed.out || true
%not-contains: test_undisposed.out
undisposed object: (
%#--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
